cs.SI, cs.NI, cs.HC, cs.CYBER, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on a crowd sensing system that relies on user contributions to provide information about WiFi hotspots. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is also a likely category as the paper discusses the implementation of a WiFi advisory system. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is relevant as the paper discusses the design of a gamification-based incentive scheme to motivate user participation. 
- cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity and Privacy) could be relevant as the paper may touch on issues related to privacy and security when collecting user data. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is a less likely category, but could be relevant as the paper may discuss the use of multimedia (e.g. images, videos) in the WiFi advisory system.
